President Muhamamdu Buhari continues his efforts to halt further depletion of the membership of the All Progressive Congress ( APC) with a meeting of all APC Senators at the Presidential Villa, tonight. The meeting BusinessDay gathered from very reliable source at the Presidential Villa, is aimed at checking further defection from the party following the defection of 15 Senators from the party to the People’s Democratic Party ( PDP) on Tuesday. The defection BusinessDay gathered is creating panic in the top echelon of the party, as more of the party members are scheduled to defect to other parties in the coming months. It is not however clear if the Senate President Bukola Saraki will be attending the meeting following rumors of his plans to also defect from the party. Saraki is however yet to make his intention public Details later….  Tony Ailemen, Abuja 